      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "The answer to the people who are insisting that this is &quot;a bad design&quot; is that it <b>had to be that way</b>.  The alternative was breaking changes to the Java language which would have required Sun/Oracle&#39;s existing (paying) customers to review billions of lines of source code.  That was not acceptable.  (That was in 2004. The amount of code review in 2018 would be 2 or 3 orders of magnitude larger.)"
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 47283,
        "reputation" : 723399,
        "user_id" : 139985,
        "user_type" : "registered",
