      "creation_date" : 1571100741,
      "post_id" : 2721557,
      "comment_id" : 103119151,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "And no it <i>won&#39;t</i> get fixed in some future version of Java because it would <i>still</i> be a massively breaking change.  This would be like the Python 2 -&gt; 3 upheaval.  Enterprise (paying) customers wouldn&#39;t stand for it.  (Read - your company&#39;s CIO ... the guy who has to find the human resources to do the work, and who decides which programming languages <i>shall be used</i> going forward.)"
