  "question_id" : 2721546,
  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2721546/why-dont-java-generics-support-primitive-types",
  "title" : "Why don&#39;t Java Generics support primitive types?",
  "body" : "<p>Why do generics in Java work with classes but not with primitive types?</p>\n\n<p>For example, this works fine:</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;Integer&gt; foo = new ArrayList&lt;Integer&gt;();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>but this is not allowed:</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;int&gt; bar = new ArrayList&lt;int&gt;();\n</code></pre>\n"
